settings.woods-content-body: The art of perfume did not emerge from France but it is the country that became the purveyor of luxury fragrances to the world. Napoleon himself indulged with exorbitant expenditures for perfume as did Josephine. The musk scent she favored to her husband’s jasmine scents lingered in her boudoir for sixty years after her death due to her excessive use of it.Despite the rise of chemical scents, it clings to the natural production of perfumes through natural extracts and decades- old methods and techniques.
settings.woods-content-additional: The Woods fragrances are produced in France at the hands of masters of the perfuming craft.
